<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56be31e6-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s2181"><num value="2181">§ 2181.</num><heading> Physical fitness of officers</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall prescribe regulations under which the physical fitness of officers to perform their duties shall be periodically determined.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56be31e7-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/88/130/s1/10/C">Pub. L. 88–130, § 1(10)(C)</ref>, <date date="1963-09-24">Sept. 24, 1963</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/77/190">77 Stat. 190</ref>, § 335; renumbered § 2181, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s112/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 112(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4216">132 Stat. 4216</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
